<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="109" type="type material">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
The type material of 
<taxonomicName genus="Crochiphora" lsidName="Crochiphora flavistriaria" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="flavistriaria">Crochiphora flavistriaria</taxonomicName>
is lost, but the illustrations (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hübner">Huebner</normalizedToken>
, 1831, pl. [96], figs 555, 556) are diagnostic and represent the form shown in Fig. 1. The type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Poaphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poaphila herbicola" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herbicola">Poaphila herbicola</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Poaphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poaphila contempta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contempta">Poaphila contempta</taxonomicName>
are lost, but the original descriptions are diagnostic and represent the forms shown in Figs 2 and 3 respectively. The female lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Poaphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poaphila perplexa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexa">Poaphila perplexa</taxonomicName>
in the MNHN labelled &quot;Javana [Savannah] Georgia/ perplexa/ Type/ Museum Paris/ 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Poaphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poaphila perplexa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexa">Poaphila perplexa</taxonomicName>
Gn. Vol. 7, 1852, p. 302, n=1755&quot; is shown in Fig. 11. The male holotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Poaphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poaphila perspicua" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspicua">Poaphila perspicua</taxonomicName>
in the BMNH labelled &quot;Type/ 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Argyrostrotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Argyrostrotis perspicua" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspicua">Argyrostrotis perspicua</taxonomicName>
.&quot; is shown in Fig. 12 and represents the same form as the original illustration of 
<taxonomicName genus="Crochiphora" lsidName="Crochiphora flavistriaria" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="flavistriaria">Crochiphora flavistriaria</taxonomicName>
. The male holotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mocis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mocis diffundens" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffundens">Mocis? diffundens</taxonomicName>
in the BMNH labelled &quot;Type/ 8. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mocis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mocis diffundens" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffundens">Mocis? diffundens</taxonomicName>
.&quot; is shown in Fig. 13. A male syntype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Phurys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phurys glans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glans">Phurys glans</taxonomicName>
in the BMNH labelled &quot;Type/ Grote Coll. 82-54./ 3129/ 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Phurys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phurys glans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glans">Phurys glans</taxonomicName>
Grote type&quot; is shown in Fig. 14. The male lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Phurys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phurys carolina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolina">Phurys carolina</taxonomicName>
in the AMNH labelled &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenée, 1852" authorityName="Guenée" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Phurys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phurys carolina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolina">Phurys carolina</taxonomicName>
Smith % type/ Nth Car., August&quot;/ Coll. J.B. Smith/ Lectotype by E.L. Todd&quot; is shown in Fig. 15.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
